The United States strongly condemns the recent terrorist attacks in Burkina Faso and expresses condolences to the families of those killed, including an American citizen. The US is working to account for all American citizens in Burkina Faso and assist the victims. The bravery of security personnel from Burkina Faso, France, and the US is commended for preventing even more loss of life. Burkina Faso has shown resilience in conducting peaceful and democratic elections, despite attempts to derail them. The US will continue to support Burkina Faso and other countries in the region in their fight against terrorism and will assist in the investigation and holding accountable those responsible for the attacks.